Steps to deploy patch
---------------------
1. Stop the connector service (If Running).
2. Navigate to the folder CONNECTOR_HOME\Tomcat\webapps\connector-manager\WEB-INF\lib.
3. Replace the existing connector-file.jar with the jar from patch.
4. Start the connector service.

Issues Fixed
------------
- Issue 16: Rename packages to have the name FileNet instead of file.
- Issue 20: Few Metadata (Document Title/ Name etc) which should be crawled by default are not getting crawled.
- Issue 21: On search result page, when we click on the hyperlink to open the Document, it gives error as the formed URL is not correct.
- Issue 22: Connector does not show any error message on GSA connector configuration page when Workplace URL is not correct.
- Issue 26: Search results not obtained because authentication and authorization fails.
- Issue 28: Documents with access rights for #AUTHENTICATED-USERS are not searched by User2 with no direct access rights on those documents.
- Issue 34: FileNet connector should be able to crawl multi-valued metadata.
- Issue 35: Timestamp is not registered correctly in the feed log file.
- Issue 36: DateLastModified and other dates are not getting fed to GSA.
- Issue 37: Incremental crawl is working fine with connector manager 2.4.0 but it is not working with 2.4.4


Known Limitations
-------------------
- Issue 11: Documents which are checked in as only minor version and don't have any major version at all, will not be crawled.
- Issue 14: Few words are displayed in English on connector Configuration page in GSA when we change the language on IE & Mozilla browsers.